	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>These are a nice, inexpensive way to help boost your CHA when selling to or buying from merchants.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been carrying a pack full of CHA gear for a long time and it has more than paid for itself.  My base CHA is 50 (I play a halfling) but with my CHA gear on it reaches 109.  With indifferent or better faction that gets me the best prices available from most vendors.<br><br>In my experience a CHA over about 100 is all you need for this.<br><br>Other good CHA kit items include gold catseye bracelets, a crude stein, and split paw necklaces.  Some of the guards on the wall in Misty Thicket drop a ring that adds 5 to CHA.  Halflings can quest for a Leatherfoot Raiders Skullcap that also adds to CHA.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shmoozo<br></td></tr>
